      "writtenOn": "2020-10-16T19:17:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I strongly recommend classes over inlining style strings via the template. How I\u0027ve handled this \u0027set of states that map to different styles in the past isn\u0027t too tedious I think. I do\nHTML:\n\u003cdiv class\u003d${jobClass(myjob)}\u003e....\u003c/div\u003e\n\nJS:\nfunction jobClass(job: Job) {\n  return `status-${job.status.replace(/\\s/g,\u0027\u0027)}`;\n}\n\nCSS:\n.status-suceeded {\n  background-color: rgb(209, 228, 188);\n}\n.....\n\nBetter organization that way, easier to find/change colors, and static validation of the CSS.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 46,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 46,
        "endChar": 26
      },
